text:
The breeze smiles lightly in her sunlit castle;  
The bee chatters in a dull, unmoved ear;  
The sweet birds flute in their heedless rhythm, --  
Ah, what wisdom has died away here!

source_text:
Light laughs the breeze in her castle of sunshine;
Babbles the bee in a stolid ear;
Pipe the sweet birds in ignorant cadence, --
Ah, what sagacity perished here!

text:
The cold rain keeps falling, the pinched worm keeps crawling,  
The rivers are rising, the thunder is tolling  
For the Year;  
The merry swallows have gone, and the lizards each one  
To its hiding place;  
Come, Months, come away;  
Wear white, black, and gray;  
Let your bright sisters play—  
You, follow the bier  
Of the dead, cold Year,  
And let her grave grow green with tear upon tear.

